BT /F1 24 Tf 0.051 0.078 0.094 rg 58 760 Td (One Working AI System Beats More AI) Tj ET
BT /F1 24 Tf 0.051 0.078 0.094 rg 58 730 Td (Architecture) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 0.051 0.078 0.094 rg 58 682 Td (A short Time to Revenue field note on reducing dropped) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 0.051 0.078 0.094 rg 58 662 Td (handoffs, copy-paste work, and wasted token spend.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 0.051 0.078 0.094 rg 58 630 Td (Most small businesses do not need a giant AI transformation program.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 0.051 0.078 0.094 rg 58 607 Td (They need one working system that can catch the work, send it to the right place,) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 0.051 0.078 0.094 rg 58 592 Td (and prove the job happened. That sounds basic because it is. It is also where many) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 0.051 0.078 0.094 rg 58 577 Td (AI projects quietly fail.) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 0.051 0.078 0.094 rg 58 554 Td (1. The real problem) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 0.051 0.078 0.094 rg 58 522 Td (The problem is usually not a lack of AI.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 0.051 0.078 0.094 rg 58 499 Td (It is the gap between tools, people, and tasks. A lead arrives in one place. Notes) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 0.051 0.078 0.094 rg 58 484 Td (live somewhere else. Someone copies context into a prompt. Another person waits) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 0.051 0.078 0.094 rg 58 469 Td (for a reply. Then nobody is fully sure whether the work moved forward.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 0.051 0.078 0.094 rg 58 446 Td (That is not an intelligence problem. It is an operations problem.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 0.051 0.078 0.094 rg 58 423 Td (More agents, dashboards, and automation layers can make that mess look impressive) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 0.051 0.078 0.094 rg 58 408 Td (without making it useful.) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 0.051 0.078 0.094 rg 58 385 Td (2. What a working system captures) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 0.051 0.078 0.094 rg 58 353 Td (A working system starts by capturing the task at the moment it appears.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 0.051 0.078 0.094 rg 58 330 Td (That means the request, the source, the owner, the context needed to act, and the) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 0.051 0.078 0.094 rg 58 315 Td (standard for a useful outcome. If those pieces are missing, the work becomes a) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 0.051 0.078 0.094 rg 58 300 Td (memory test.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 0.051 0.078 0.094 rg 58 277 Td (The first question is simple: where does the task enter the business, and what) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 0.051 0.078 0.094 rg 58 262 Td (information is lost before anyone acts on it?) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 0.051 0.078 0.094 rg 58 239 Td (3. What the system routes) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 0.051 0.078 0.094 rg 58 207 Td (The system should route work to the right person, agent, or tool.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 0.051 0.078 0.094 rg 58 184 Td (Not every task needs a model. Some tasks need a checklist. Some need a human) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 0.051 0.078 0.094 rg 58 169 Td (decision. Some need a known automation. The system earns its keep when it knows) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 0.051 0.078 0.094 rg 58 154 Td (the difference.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 0.051 0.078 0.094 rg 58 131 Td (Good routing reduces copy-paste work. It also stops expensive model calls from) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 0.051 0.078 0.094 rg 58 116 Td (being used as glue between badly connected steps.) Tj ET
BT /F2 8 Tf 0.318 0.376 0.408 rg 58 32 Td (Time to Revenue) Tj ET
endstream
